sentences.original:
(h) Poorly trimmed or mechanically damaged unit – a unit in which:
i) the stem end is very ragged leaving a heel extending more than 10 mm beyond the point of attachment of the lowest outer leaves;
ii) 4 or more outer leaves have been damaged such that only the petioles remain attached to the stem;
iii) the stem extends more than 10 mm below the point of attachment of the lowest outer leaves; or
iv) the appearance is damaged to an extent that the sprout is lacerated, can be separated easily into two pieces, or more than 25 percent of its volume has been removed.

